Job Description:

AUA Extension welcomes applications from qualified candidates for teaching General English in Goris. Potential applicants are encouraged to carefully review the below position requirements before deciding to put forth their application. The success of AUA Extension courses relies primarily on the instructors’ commitment to student success through interactive and student-centered instruction.

Job responsibilities
Teach the course following the approved syllabus and learning objectives;
Develop a detailed course plan to share with the students at start of class and hold regular class/office hours accordingly;
Assign homework and provide feedback on student performance on a consistent basis;
Ensure that all quizzes, tests, assignments, and exams are graded and returned to students in a timely manner, duly marked with constructive feedback;
Find, study, and recommend new teaching strategies that may help improve learning. These may include materials from different sources that could be useful in fulfilling the learning objectives;
Assess, record and report on the development, progress, attendance and classroom performance of students;
Provide guidance and advice to students on educational matters, also providing assistance to ensure the quality of external sources;
Ensure high standards of professional practice and quality of teaching;
Perform related duties, as assigned.
Required qualifications
University degree in a relevant field. 
Excellent command of the English Language.
At least 2 years of teaching experience.
Required candidate level
Not defined
Personal skills
Teaching skills
Additional Information:

Please submit your CV and brief Cover Letter, with contact information of three references via our platform.

