Job Description:

IP Engineer is responsible for the IP Transport Network (TN) operations, maintenance and reconfiguration works. He/She ensures the uninterrupted operation of the IP TN sub-systems, IP network monitoring system, suggests and implements approved changes.

Job responsibilities
Ensure the operation of the IP routing and switching systems (IP/MPLS), the correctness of the configuration and database;
Cooperate with the equipment vendors for neutralizing defects and issues;
Ensure availability of fresh backups from the network elements for emergency recovery;
Organize the works for new nodes integration;
Ensure and supervise the correspondence of the IP TN sub-system configuration with the project design data;
Prepare and maintain the network design documents, diagrams and schemes;
Analyze the alarms registered on the network and undertake actions for issues elimination;
Monitor and analyze network elements statistical data;
Prepare and provide periodical and on-demand reports;
Participate in IP TN upgrade, design and budget preparation;
Conduct analysis of new equipment received from vendors, make selection of equipment, prepare recommendations.
Required qualifications
Higher Education in relevant sphere;
3 years of relevant work experience;
Knowledge of IP network architectures, systems (LAN, WAN), IP routing principles and protocols (OSPF, BGP, IS-IS), IP/MLPS technologies;
Excellent technical and PC skills;
Skills in the sphere of IP networks and UNIX/Linux operation systems;
Good knowledge of the Armenian, Russian and English languages;
Ability to learn new technologies;
Ability to work under pressure;
Analytical and reporting skills;
Team-work and cooperation;
Problem solving skills;
Business communication skills;
Ability to work under load and outside working hours (night hours).
Required candidate level
Mid level
